ref: Jour: Physical Review, Part C, Nuclear Physics, Vol.4, p.1130 (1971)
title: Differential Elastic Cross Sections For Protons Between 10 and 22 MeV on Ca-40.

x4freetext: Differential Elastic Cross Sections For Protons

x4codes.hlp: Los Alamos National Laboratory, NM, United States of America
Oak Ridge National Laboratory, Oak Ridge, TN, United States of America

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Physical Review, Part C, Nuclear Physics, Vol.4, p.1130 (1971)

x4freetext: Two Targets were Used For Those Measurements. Both
Targets were Made from the Same Foil of Isotopically
Enriched Ca-40 Containing 99.97% of Ca-40. The Areal
Densities of these Targets were 2.67+-0.08 Mg/Cm**2
A  500-Mu  Surface-Barrier  Detector  For  the  Delta-E
Detector and a Lithium-Drifted Silicon Detector For the
E-Detector.   The  Depth of the E-Detector was 2 mm at
Lower  Energies  and  3  mm  at  Higher  Energies.   In
Addition  to the E+Delta-E, There was a Second Detector
Used As a Monitor For the System.

x4codes.hlp: Los Alamos National Laboratory, NM, United States of America
